Key stakeholders:

- Raf (head of product, desktop browser)
- Stefanos (ML researcher)
- Brad (head of design)
- Agustín (product designer)
- April (sr. UX researcher)

---

{% table %}
- **Research Question** (what we want to know)
- **Rationale** (why it’s important)
---
- What value to users derived from other browser-based AI chatbots?
- Ensure that Brave delivers the same value
---
- What are the user pain-points/missing features in existing/competing AI chatbots?
- Finding features to build that go beyond what competitors are offering.
---
- How do users use browser-based chatbots for writing and what are the unmet opportunities in this space?
- Stakeholders believed that having a writing assistant will make the chatbot more appealing to users - we wanted to test this hypothesis.
{% /table %}

# Method and Sample

Ideal participant: Someone who regularly uses browser-based AI chatbots for work and personal use cases.

Sample size: 17 interviews (saturation)

Method: Semi-structured interview + Observation

Interview focus points:

- What do participants use AI chatbots for?
- Observe how they use chatbots as they explain their usage.
- When do participants go to chatbots vs. when they turn to web search?
- How do participants use the different features in a chatbot - chat history etc.?
- How have participants used chatbots to write

